 not have the necessary traffic signs yourself, you can rent one from a private company.<br />\r\nYou can find companies in the Yellow Pages under the heading 'road and yard signs'.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>When to place the signs?</strong><br />\r\nYou should place the traffic signs on the public domain <strong>at least 48 hours before the start</strong> of the move or works.<br />\r\n<strong>If there is no work on certain days, the signs should be covered </strong>.<br />\r\nAs soon as the works are over, the signs should be removed.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Passing on number plates</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>When placing no parking signs, you must provide the number plates of the vehicles currently parked there.<br />\r\nYou must immediately <a href=\"https://eforms.gent.be/Productie4.0/formulier/sc_kennisgevingnummerplaten.aspx\">send</a> these number plates, together with the place, date and time, <a href=\"https://eforms.gent.be/Productie4.0/formulier/sc_kennisgevingnummerplaten.aspx\">online</a> to the police.<br />\r\n<strong>Concrete instructions for reporting number plates will be sent to you along with your permit.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>If cars are parked between the plates during the licensed period, please contact the Police (101). Only the Police have the authority to look up the details of number plates.<br />\r\n<strong>The Police will act on problems with incorrectly parked cars only if they were notified in good time (i.e. 48 hours in advance).</strong></p>"
